<br>
Stat buffs do not effect pets, except in the case of DEX which will cause your pet to proc more often.<br>
<br>
Pure HP/AC buffs are noticeable and do work.<br>
<br>
No idea about items, although it wouldnt surprise me if focus effects and the like did not work on them. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://cyberseth.com/~rhaug/girlball.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ozommo>Ozommo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/31/02 6:20:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nikatjef>nikatjef</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/02 6:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/nikatjef/Everquest/Rogue.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet FACTS - SOE/VI Please Acknowledge. </span><hr size=1> Ozommo,<br>
