<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I dueled my Shaman and Mage... If I nuked the pet I can heal it with my shaman to full health.. I can apply shaman HP buffs and see the effect after I nuke it in a DUEL. You can cast any spell you like on the person and their pets you are dueling in a PVE environment.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
   No, the Mage cannot heal their own pet, nor can the Shaman heal dogdog.   Perhaps what you meant to say when you said...<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And yes, You can buff pets while in a duel.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
  Was that, your opponent can heal your pet while in a duel.  And though this may be possible, it is easily proven that you cannot heal/buff your own pet while in a duel.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I know that +ATK has an effect and logs to prove it, I also know that DEX plays NO role on innate procs (Like the epic pet innate proc). Now, DEX MIGHT effect Beastlord Spell procs casted on pets.. But, don't assume that it has an effect on innate proc's or weapon proc's on pets.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
   Strangely enough, I do equip my warder with proc'ing weapons as well, specifically things like Velium Daggers, Fist Of Ixiblat, etc.  So yes, I have seen a difference in proc rates for weapons as well as proc buffs.<br>
<br>
   That said however, I have often debated whether Mage pets actually proc or cast.   Personally, I am of the belief that the epic and earth pets cast, the air and water pets proc.   Because of this belief, I DEX buff the air pets when my friends summon them and I have noticed, albeit visually only, an increased rate of stuns.<br>
<br>
   Something that many people seem to lose sight of when talking about this subject is that no one really knows what the stats do.  For example, according to Rangers Glade and Safehouse, the difference between 100STR and 255STR is a grand total of 3-5% DPS difference.   According to Monkly Biz and Steel Warrior, the difference between 100AGI and 255AGI is a grand total of 4% Damage evasion, and 2% damage mitigation.  Also when I +STA buff myself, I see a grand total of +30 Max HP or ~2%.<br>
<br>
   In the first two, we are talking changes of 155 points, and at most we are seeing a difference of 5%.  As such, we can't really tell if STR helps players, other than by raising the amount they can carry as the 3-5% could easily be attributed to noise.<br>
<br>
   As far as the stamina goes, as I said, a difference of 2%, which I personally regen back within 12 seconds, however, my warder has, according to VI/SoE, 12 times my regen.   Is 30HP of his 2500HP going to even be noticable when he is regening 30+ per tick?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You seem to be in a state of denial<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
   Not denial so much as 'Prove it'.  The Crucible has run hundreds of tests, and they still haven't agreed that STA has &quot;no&quot; affect.  You call it fact, I call it theory.  The fact is, unless when can see our pet's and warder's stats, we have no way of knowing/proving the truth, as such, they can't be claimed as fact.<br>
