<br>
I know AGI has a very noticeable effect on pets, especially the earth pet (obviously).  The air pet becomes near impossible to hit with extra AGI on.  So, we know AGI works.<br>
<br>
I haven't seen an effect of STA on pets.  I use a 60 shaman to two-box a lot and I've never really noticed any difference with adding stamina.  <br>
<br>
STR seems to have an obvious effect.  Parse the average hit with and without Burnout on.  You'll probably notice a difference.<br>
<br>
I haven't really toyed around with DEX too much because I can't summon weapons that are based around this.  Yes, I am too low of a level to summon Blade of Walnan's.  The only real way to tell is to summon a pet raw with just Burnout and parse him.  Then, parse him with all the DEX buffs you can imagine (items, shaman buffs, etc).  <br>
<br>
So far, I've noticed added AGI makes the biggest difference with pets.  Cast &quot;Deleriously Nimble&quot;, a +70agi shaman buff, on your pet and notice that your pet will tank for ages without taking any damage.  This is with air pets as well.  <br>
