Text:<br>
<br>
The testing methadology used in this thread is reasonably sound, but flawed in that it relies on low-level pets and people generally cannot agree that the buffs will have any significant effect on said pets.  Why not retry the tests on a level 19 pet?  It should still have sufficiently low hp to make the results visible.  Or a level 49 pet?  This will make the HP differences harder to see, of course, but might help with the testing of the other things (like the effect of AGI / STR / DEX).<br>
<br>
Interesting reading, regardless.<br>
<br>
My personal experience is that STA has no particular effect on my pet; I cast it anyway, though.  It may not help, but it won't hurt either (except my mana pool, but heh, I'm a shaman).<br>
